The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attack at Istanbul's Ataturk International Airport in Turkey. The attack, which killed and injured many people, is similar to the attack on Brussels Airport earlier this year. The airport is seen as a symbol of international connections and unity. The US offers its condolences to the families of the victims and wishes a quick recovery to those injured. The US reaffirms its support for Turkey, a NATO ally and partner, as well as its commitment to fighting terrorism alongside other friends and allies globally.